column1: Our national response to the spread of COVID-19 cannot and should not be about politics. We must work together across party lines to help our nation recover and heal. https://t.co/elTe8WFyz4 https://t.co/UHGwwRopIX

The best campaigns shine a light on important & often neglected people/issues. Hunger in our community is exactly that. COVID has touched everyone & if you were already living on the edge it very well could have pushed you off.  (This post is part of Darcy's Twitter takeover) https://t.co/D4sFm8oPKa

Small businesses are one of the lifelines of our County. They create jobs and strengthen the community bonds between us all. But with COVID small biz has been hit extra hard and are fighting to stay afloat.  (This post is part of Jani Hitchen's Twitter takeover) https://t.co/y38i5H65tv

COVID is one of the biggest threats our communities are facing right now. As a science teacher I know we need to use science & evidence-based solutions to end this pandemic strengthen our economy and reopen our schools.  (This post is part of Jani Hitchen's Twitter takeover) https://t.co/LTo7XNat36
Here’s what’s on the ballot in 35 days: - Truth - Dignity  - Respect - Health care  - COVID recovery  Tonight’s debate made clear that we need change - we need to elect @JoeBiden. #Debate2020

The COVID-19 crisis has changed the world as we know it as well as upending the finances of countless working people. That's why last week I called on the Federal Housing Finance Agency to delay refinancing fees for the duration of the pandemic. https://t.co/EuqkjeRqBS https://t.co/ZJsdF2FxVa

The COVID-19 crisis has had a staggering impact on our communities. The Worker Relief and Security Act will help ensure states workers businesses and families have a little certainty in uncertain times. https://t.co/njyI4SlkPs https://t.co/WTx6iDaJfg

Derek has worked with the building trades and our community tirelessly to navigate through the COVID-19 pandemic. He has kept an open line of communication with Labor and community leaders.  Thank you for your support Chuck!   https://t.co/aZTFBJQbKe

Thanks to Social Security Works WA for the terrific conversation yesterday & your partnership as we work to protect & expand benefits! I'm working to pass meaningful bills like the Social Security 2100 Act & Social Security COVID-19 Correction & Equity Act to protect retirees. https://t.co/exo2lTerpt

Tribal governments have been forced to move their governmental services online due to the COVID-19 crisis. I am calling for the next relief bill to include critical cybersecurity funding for all impacted communities. https://t.co/IFqvID6v8R https://t.co/4lJP41xvA2

Because of the COVID-19 crisis many individuals who saved up for a planned medical expense might lose those funds because they can't access the care before the end of the year. My new bill will ensure folks can avoid losing their FSA savings. https://t.co/hP3irQpmFb

I am calling on the administration to prioritize a comprehensive plan at a national level to increase COVID-19 testing. We only have one shot to get this right and we need to make sure states have the support they need. https://t.co/Lb5nglUoqJ https://t.co/DcU4I9H6WK

The Payroll Protection Program ran out of funds just two weeks into this crisis. My bipartisan bill will ensure local businesses will be able to continue to pay their employees during the coronavirus economic downturn. https://t.co/htbTgoztzR https://t.co/YBr2UghBSj

I am calling for $400 million in funding to help states deal with cyber threats during COVID-19. Right now state & local jurisdictions are implementing COVID-19 relief putting local governments under even more strain. We need to prioritize security. https://t.co/bpZtRGDY9k https://t.co/5XVtztWLfm

Relief shouldn't have an "end date" with so much still uncertain. Automatic relief will help make sure Washington families and businesses impacted by COVID-19 will continue to receive the support they need. https://t.co/OgRalYFnel https://t.co/XLO18amK14

According to the CDC as many as 25 percent of people infected with the novel coronavirus are asymptomatic. It is crucial that we all continue to #StayHomeStaySafe if you are able. https://t.co/z4Os0Mr8S7 https://t.co/OrFK3llxRV
